<br>
For a little back ground...<br>
<br>
I went to rez an old &quot;friend&quot; of mine named Rellins.  I had known him for a long time, and talked to him quite frequently.  <br>
<br>
I had just purchased a new horse the day before, and he commented on it, asked me a few questions...etc.  Then he asked if he could try it out.  I hesitated, because I would normally never be so naive, but I thought...well I've knonw him long enough, he wouldn't possibly have the nerve to steal from me.  But I was wrong.  He took my horse and camped.<br>
<br>
I was so upset, I didn't know what to do I just sat there and waited for him to come back.  I never expected that he would!!  He logged back in a few moments later, I sent him several unanswered tells...and he began running from me.  I gated back to pok, figuring there was nothing to do but warn people.  I shouted what had happened, and learned he had done it before...if only I had known <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
In the meantime we found he had moved into the bazaar, and my husband went there and started shouting what had happend as well.  What happened next was something I shall never forget and will forever be the most amazing EQ day of my life.<br>
<br>
People were really upset about this and got a collection together.  Everyone petitioned.  In seconds, and I do mean seconds, I had more than enough to buy the horse again.  I couldn't keep up with the tells and trades hehe.  I want to name everyone personally, but seriously there were so many people that donated to the fund, that shouted, that petitioned, I could never name them all. THANK YOU ALL SO MUCH.<br>
<br>
I wish I had better words to use, or something real beautiful to say about the whole thing, but I have been through so many emotions in the last few hours, I am drained <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I am forever in the debt to everyone that helped me.  That was so amazing of everyone.<br>
<br>
